### Explore the YARN Cluster

msg.data: Explore the YARN Cluster

paragraphs.title: 1 - Visit the YARN Resource Manager
paragraphs.text:
%md
In a web browser on your remote desktop, reach the YARN Resource Manager (RM) UI. In Cloudera Manager select `YARN` from the Services menu on the left side. 
This will open the YARN summary. From the Quick Linds pull down select the `Resource Manager UI`.

msg.data:
In a web browser on your remote desktop, reach the YARN Resource Manager (RM) UI. In Cloudera Manager select YARN from the Services menu on the left side.
This will open the YARN summary. From the Quick Linds pull down select the Resource Manager UI.

paragraphs.title: 2 - View the available metrics
paragraphs.text:
%md
Review the **Cluster Overview** section, this displays summary information on the amount of memory used and available in each YARN queue.

msg.data: Review the Cluster Overview section, this displays summary information on the amount of memory used and available in each YARN queue.

paragraphs.title: 3 - View the list of applications
paragraphs.text:
%md
Click the **Applications** tab from the menu at the top of the page, it will display a list of applications in the cluster. Experiment with the filtering on 
the left-hand side of the page.

msg.data:

paragraphs.title: 4 - Open the Applications Manager page
paragraphs.text:
%md
Click the link for one of the applications. This takes you down to the ApplicationsMasters display page. This page provoides summary information about the 
application, such as resources used and logs.

spark-submit /home/training/training_materials/devsh/exercises/yarn/wordcount.py /devsh_loudacre/kb/*
